She had a few fish now, and prepared them before adding a few spices and frying them.  She crushed some fruit and made a juice from them.  She set more fruit into a bowl to go with the fish, and place warm sugary hot cross buns beside the plates.  She fixed some eggs the way Choco loved, and as she set the last of the food on the table, he entered.<br>
&quot;Good morning, my darling.&quot;  he took her in his arms and kissed her passionately.  He was damp from a bath he took after his sparring session.  His muscles rippled as he placed his equipment in a cabinet above another table.<br>
&quot;Breakfast is ready, my love.&quot; she smiled.  He smiled back, and sighed at her lovingly.  She was so beautiful, and he loved her more than his own life.<br>
Lenore glanced at her husband while they ate.  His hair had grown a little longer, and he tied part of it back in a leather thong.  The gold embroidered patch was eventually replaced by a plain black one, but he looked no less dashing.  She sighed.  She loved him so much.<br>
<br>
As the last of the breakfast dishes were cleaned and put away, Choco had dressed in plain leather clothing as well.  Lenore suggested they take a walk, maybe stop by the Fool's Gold to visit Blinza.  <br>
As they entered the establishment, Lenore heard a very familiar voice coming from upstairs. <br>
&quot;That sounded like Magpye,&quot; she said to Choco.  <br>
&quot;Yes, it did.  Shall we go see?&quot;  she grinned.  He knew her too well.<br>
&quot;Yes, let's.&quot;<br>
They climbed up the narrow stairs and into a small common room.  And there, at a table with her back to the stairs, was Magpye.  Lenore grinned broadly, and snuck up behind her.  She gently covered the halfling's eyes, and spoke softly.<br>
&quot;Guess who?&quot; <p>Lenore Bravehard
Preserver of Druidic Lore
Devoted wife and faithful companion of Choco Bravehard

