..</span><hr size=1> &quot;Ah, many things,&quot; the hafling woman said, smiling.  &quot;My legs may tire more easily now, but my feet are as itchy as ever.  These last few seasons I have been exploring up on the moon...such a wonderous place!&quot;<br>
<br>
A brief sadness touched her eyes.  &quot;Many old friends have dropped out of sight over the years,&quot; she said.  &quot;Journeyed to lands unknown, or retired from adventuring, or simply vanished from sight.  Yet I have made many new friends as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I have spent many long seasons in the frozen lands of Velious.  Many find the dirfted snows and frozen icey lands there too sere and empty, but I recall my youth in Everfrost and am exhilerated by the bright icey days and the wild wind-driven blizzards.  Iztariani, too, enjoys the calm emptiness of the frozen lands, though Snoww has a rather more...errrr..cosmopolitan nature.&quot;  She smiled.  &quot;She is forever badgering us to make journeys elsewhere...the jungles of Kunark, the plains of Karana, the wild mountains of Odus.  And my feet do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> itch</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> so, that I must admit it is not that hard for her to be convincing.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Some times I think of retiring to a quieter life, but then I meet a new companion for a time in my travels, or find a place to explore I've never been before, and the world is a new and interesting place again.&quot;<br>
<br>
Magpye flashed a brilliant smile at Lenore and Choco.  &quot;So, tell me, what have you two been up to since last we met?&quot;<br>
