she really didn't have her parent to talk to, as he always seemed to be absent.<br>
&quot;I like the snowy climes of Velious as well, the stark beauty, and adapting to the harsh conditions of living there.  The city of Thurgadin is most unusual, and beautiful at the same time.  My daughter has recently relocated there for now, so at least she is away from Freeport.  I know she is a grown woman, but she will always be my little girl.  And I worry.  Her lifemate is good for her, and I know he keeps her safe, but I don't trust the militia as far as I can throw them.  Ever since my near execution, I seldom venture there anymore, and it is usually under extremely rare circumstances.&quot;  She shuddered at that distant memory, and Choco placed an arm around her.<br>
She touched his hand, and looked at him to assure him she was fine.<br>
&quot;Well, enough of those gloomy memories.&quot; she said brightly.<br>
&quot;I am glad to see you again, my friend.  Should you happen to see a human wandering around with a big ogre comapnion, you know it is my daughter.&quot;  <p>Lenore Bravehard
