<br>
&quot;In Thurgadin I met her...both her and her ogrish friend.  Tis well that dear Gogak taught me not to fear all of ogre-kind many years ago, or I would have been quite terrified by Gug...he is most ferocious looking!&quot;<br>
<br>
Magpye laughed again at Lenore's startled look.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, she is how I knew to seek you and Choco here, among my own small kin.  Many a long year has it been since last I visited here...the place teems with memories, and some few of them are painful.  Even the thought of returning to talk with my dear master Reebo has not been enough to lure me back.  But, hearing from Jolene that this was where you now nested, why, Snoww and I packed and travelled here forthwith...twas just last night that the four of us, Jolene and Gug and Snoww and I, lifted glasses together in Thurgadin.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I do think I will linger here a few days before I leave again,&quot; Magpye added.  &quot;There are as many good memories here as bad.  And I should seek word of my father, I have not heard from him in far too long.  Like my friend Snoww, he is a follower of not strickly legal ways, but, I must admit, he has not her fine touch with things.  I always fear that he will be found out, and imprisoned somewhere for his light-fingered habits.&quot;<br>
<br>
The concerned frown dissapeared from Magpye's face as she smiled at someone behind Lenore's back.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, here comes Snoww now,&quot; she said.<br>
