&quot;I am glad you mentioned my daughter, Magpye.  While I still worry for her safety in and around Freeport, I know she can hold her own against them.  And I am glad she is well.&quot;<br>
&quot;As I am happy to hear it as well.&quot; Choco added.<br>
<br>
Around the noon hour, Lenore announced that her and Choco needed to be travelling again.<br>
&quot;We have been here 3 days, and got any supplies we needed, and it is time for us to go.  Oh, it was so wonderful to see you again.&quot;  She hugged Magpye.  It was nice to have friends, but it was special to have ones that mattered in life.<br>
Choco also hugged the perky little halfling, telling her to not be away too long.<br>
&quot;I'll try not to,&quot; Magpye said with a dimpled grin.<br>
&quot;It was also a pleasure to make your acquaintence, Snoww.&quot;  Lenore said.<br>
&quot;As it was mine, also.&quot;  Snow replied.  Lenore and Choco said their goodbyes and headed out of the tavern.  They made their way back to their little hut, and tidied things up, and dressed back into their normal travelling armor and clothing.<br>
They exited their home, and passed near the tavern as Snoww and Magpye were leaving it.  They said their goodbyes one last time, and Lenore called forth a portal.  Just before her and Choco stepped into it, he scooped Lenore into his arms, much to the amusement of Magpye and Snoww.  Then the portal closed, and all was quiet again. <p>Lenore Bravehard
